---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Bertazzoni Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Italian Range & Oven Specialists";
const description = "Expert Bertazzoni appliance repair in Los Angeles. Master, Heritage, Professional & Modern Series — ranges, ovens, refrigerators, dishwashers. Same-day service, OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Bertazzoni Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-bertazzoni-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Bertazzoni Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Dishwasher Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Bertazzoni Hood Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Bertazzoni appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Bertazzoni repairs run $175–$580. Igniter replacement, door gasket, or temperature sensor work is on the lower end. Control board or gas valve replacement runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service all Bertazzoni series — Master, Heritage, Professional, and Modern?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — all four design series. Master, Heritage, Professional, and Modern share the same core technical platform, so our diagnosis and parts approach is consistent across series. The differences between them are primarily aesthetic: panel designs, handle styles, and color options. We service all series and handle colored panel installations with appropriate care."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair Bertazzoni appliances in color — Arancio, Rosso, Giallo and others?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Bertazzoni's color-painted panels (including Arancio orange, Rosso red, Giallo yellow, and 15+ other colors) require specific handling during service — standard steel tools can chip or scratch the painted finish. We use protective covers on all color-panel appliances and handle panel removal and reinstallation with the care that colored enamel demands."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where is Bertazzoni made?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Bertazzoni is still manufactured in Guastalla, in the Emilia-Romagna region of northern Italy — the same region that produces Ferrari, Lamborghini, and Maserati. The company has been family-owned for five generations since 1882 and continues to produce all appliances in Italy."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are the most common Bertazzoni failures in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Igniter failure on gas burners is the most common — LA coastal salt air accelerates ceramic corrosion on Bertazzoni's sealed burner igniters. Oven temperature calibration drift and convection fan issues are second and third. Control board faults appear on older models. We carry common Bertazzoni igniter and temperature sensor components on the truck."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Bertazzoni dual-fuel ranges?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Bertazzoni dual-fuel ranges combine a gas cooktop with an electric oven — two independent systems that require separate diagnostic approaches. The gas side uses Bertazzoni's sealed burner system with specific igniter geometry. The electric oven side uses a bake element and convection system with its own control board. We diagnose each system independently."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .series-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .series-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px 16px; }
  .series-name { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .series-desc { font-size: 12px; color: #666; line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .series-colors { font-size: 11px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .color-strip { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .color-chip { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 5px 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); background: #fff; }
  .color-dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-italy { border-color: #2a5ea5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-italy .tip-label { color: #2a5ea5; }
  .tip-color { border-color: #c8820a; background: #fff8f0; }
  .tip-color .tip-label { color: #c8820a; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-coastal { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-color { background: #c8820a; }
  .tag-dual { background: #444; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .series-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Bertazzoni Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Bertazzoni Repair.<br/>
        <span>Emilia-Romagna</span><br/>
        Since 1882.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Bertazzoni comes from the same corner of Italy that makes Ferrari — Guastalla, Emilia-Romagna, family-owned for five generations. Master, Heritage, Professional, Modern — four design series on one platform we know cold. Arancio, Rosso, Verde: colored panels handled with the care they require.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">Same</div><div class="badge-label">Day Service</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">OEM</div><div class="badge-label">Bertazzoni Parts</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">90-Day</div><div class="badge-label">Warranty</div></div>
      <div class="hero-badge"><div class="badge-num">$89</div><div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">All 4 Design Series</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Color Panel Safe Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Genuine Bertazzoni OEM Parts</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Bertazzoni</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">142 Years. Same Family. Same Factory in Emilia-Romagna.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Francesco Bertazzoni founded his company in Guastalla in 1882 — originally making precision weighing scales for the local cheese industry, then inventing a wood-burning stove for heating railway cars that spread across Italy. The company has been making professional-grade cooking appliances in the same region ever since, through five generations of the same family. Guastalla is in Emilia-Romagna: the same northern Italian province that produces Ferrari, Lamborghini, Maserati, and Ducati. There's something about the precision manufacturing culture of this region that shows in how Bertazzoni builds its products.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Bertazzoni arrived in the United States in 2007 — relatively late for a brand with this heritage — and found a strong market among design-forward LA kitchens that wanted European aesthetics with professional performance. Today the full product lineup includes ranges, cooktops, wall ovens, refrigerators, dishwashers, and ventilation hoods, organized into four design series that share the same mechanical platform.
    </p>

    <div class="series-grid">
      <div class="series-card"><div class="series-name">Master</div><div class="series-desc">Bertazzoni's flagship professional line. Stainless, maximum BTUs, commercial kitchen presence. The range serious cooks choose when they want performance above all.</div><div class="series-colors">Stainless · Black · White</div></div>
      <div class="series-card"><div class="series-name">Heritage</div><div class="series-desc">The iconic Italian range with color. Retro-inspired design, chrome knobs, curved feet — available in the full Bertazzoni color palette. The most visually distinctive series.</div><div class="series-colors">18+ Colors Available</div></div>
      <div class="series-card"><div class="series-name">Professional</div><div class="series-desc">Modern professional aesthetics with dual-fuel capability. Clean lines, precision controls, designed for kitchens where performance and design carry equal weight.</div><div class="series-colors">Stainless · Black · White</div></div>
      <div class="series-card"><div class="series-name">Modern</div><div class="series-desc">Bertazzoni's contemporary minimalist line. Flat fronts, recessed handles, seamless integration into modern kitchen architecture. Clean European design vocabulary.</div><div class="series-colors">Stainless · Black · White</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-color" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🎨 Color Panels — Our Service Protocol</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Bertazzoni's Heritage series is famous for its 18+ color options — Arancio (orange), Rosso (red), Giallo (yellow), Verde (green), Blu (blue), Nero (matte black), and more. These enamel-painted panels chip, scratch, and scuff in ways that stainless steel doesn't. We apply non-abrasive protective covers on all color-panel Bertazzoni appliances before any service work begins. Panel removal and reinstallation is done with felt-backed tools only. We won't leave a visible scratch on a Bertazzoni Arancio Heritage range — that finish is the reason someone bought it.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Bertazzoni Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All four design series, all appliance categories. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Range &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni gas, dual-fuel, and electric ranges across all series — 30", 36", and 48" configurations. The Master series reaches 19,000 BTU on the power burner, which creates specific igniter thermal stress similar to other high-BTU Italian ranges. Bertazzoni's sealed burner design has a specific cap geometry that affects how igniters are positioned — OEM igniters matter for correct spark alignment.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter failure · burner won't light · oven temperature off · dual-fuel switching fault · convection fan · door gasket · control board · gas valve · color panel care</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni single and double wall ovens — gas, electric, and combination. The convection system uses a fan-plus-element configuration similar to other Italian luxury brands. When the convection fan fails, one side of the oven consistently runs hotter — a pattern owners often attribute to rack position before calling us. We test fan speed and element resistance independently before recommending parts.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: uneven baking · convection fan failure · temperature sensor · door gasket · self-cleaning lock · heating element · control board · door hinge</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni column and French door refrigerators. Bertazzoni's refrigeration line is panel-ready, integrating into custom cabinetry with flush installation. The condenser coil placement in Bertazzoni column refrigerators requires specific access technique — we know the service panel locations and don't need to pull the unit from its recess on most calls.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · temperature fluctuation · ice maker · water dispenser · door gasket · condenser service · compressor · defrost system · panel-ready installation care</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Dishwasher Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni fully integrated and semi-integrated dishwashers. Bertazzoni's dishwasher line uses European-style wash systems with high water temperature and specific filter configurations. LA hard water scale accumulates in the spray arms and wash circuit faster than the European market Bertazzoni calibrates for — we address the scale along with whatever caused the immediate failure.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not draining · not cleaning · spray arm scaling · door latch · control board · water inlet · pump motor · circulation pump · LA hard water service</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">💨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Ventilation Hood Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni wall, island, and built-in ventilation hoods designed to match each design series. The hood blower motor and speed selector are the most common failure points. Bertazzoni hoods use a specific baffle filter system that requires periodic cleaning to maintain airflow — a restricted filter causes the motor to work harder and fail earlier. We clean the baffle simultaneously with every hood motor service call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: blower motor failure · speed selector fault · lighting · baffle filter restriction · duct connection · noise · electronic controls</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔵</div>
        <div class="service-name">Induction Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Bertazzoni's induction cooktops — single zone and full-surface configurations. Induction zone failures on Bertazzoni cooktops most commonly trace to the inverter board for that zone, not the glass surface. We test each zone's inverter circuit independently before ordering the glass assembly, which costs significantly more. Most Bertazzoni induction failures are board-level, same-day fixable.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: zone dead or intermittent · inverter board fault · error codes · glass surface damage assessment · control panel · temperature regulation · fan noise</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-italy" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">💧 LA Hard Water + Bertazzoni — What It Means</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Bertazzoni's appliances are calibrated for Italian and European water hardness — typically 100–200 ppm. Los Angeles water runs 250–400 ppm. The practical consequence: scale accumulates in Bertazzoni dishwasher spray arms, refrigerator water filters, and steam-assisted oven systems faster than the maintenance intervals assume. We factor local water hardness into every Bertazzoni service call — cleaning scale that isn't the immediate cause of the failure but will cause the next one.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bertazzoni Engineering — And What Breaks</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Four design series, one technical platform. Understanding Bertazzoni's approach explains the failure modes — and why Italian-range experience matters.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Sealed Burner System</strong> — Bertazzoni ranges use a sealed burner with a specific cap geometry and igniter positioning. The 19,000 BTU power burner creates higher thermal cycling stress than standard residential burners. Coastal LA salt air accelerates ceramic igniter tip corrosion on all high-BTU Italian ranges — we inspect and proactively replace igniters before they fail completely on every Bertazzoni service call near the coast.</li>
        <li><strong>Dual-Fuel Architecture</strong> — Bertazzoni's dual-fuel ranges combine a gas cooktop with an electric convection oven — two independent systems. The gas side uses the sealed burner igniter system; the electric oven has its own bake element, convection fan, and control board. When a dual-fuel Bertazzoni shows two symptoms simultaneously, we determine whether they're related (a power surge, for example) or independent failures before ordering any parts.</li>
        <li><strong>Convection System (All Series)</strong> — Bertazzoni ovens use a fan-assisted convection system with the fan mounted in the oven rear wall. Fan failures are quiet — the oven heats but baking results become uneven before the owner realizes the fan is the cause. We test fan speed and current draw on every Bertazzoni oven service call, even when convection isn't the stated complaint.</li>
        <li><strong>Color Panel Construction</strong> — Heritage series colors are enamel-painted over steel panels with a specific paint formulation. The enamel is harder than standard paint but chips at impact and scratches with abrasive contact. Service requires felt-backed tools for panel contact and protective covers for adjacent surfaces. The front panel is structural — we reinstall it with factory torque to avoid rattling after service.</li>
        <li><strong>Induction Inverter Zones</strong> — Each induction zone on a Bertazzoni cooktop has a dedicated inverter board that converts line power to the high-frequency magnetic field. Zone failures almost always trace to the inverter board, not the glass ceramic surface. The glass is expensive; the board is a fraction of the cost. We test inverter current for each zone before any surface assessment.</li>
        <li><strong>Coordinated Ecosystem</strong> — Bertazzoni designs its appliances to work as a visually coordinated suite — range, hood, refrigerator, dishwasher all match in finish and design language. When a homeowner has a full Bertazzoni kitchen, we're familiar with the complete lineup. Suite service is our most efficient call type — we know where every service panel is on every Bertazzoni appliance.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🇮🇹 Emilia-Romagna Engineering</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Bertazzoni is manufactured in Guastalla, 30 miles from Modena — where Ferrari and Maserati are built, and where Ducati motorcycles come from. This isn't a coincidence. The Emilia-Romagna region has a precision manufacturing culture that influences how Bertazzoni tolerances its burner caps, how the stainless is finished, and why a 15-year-old Bertazzoni Heritage range still functions precisely when it's been properly maintained. These appliances are engineered to last and worth repairing.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#160a0a; border-color:var(--red); margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label">🎨 Color Heritage — Why It Shows Up in LA</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Los Angeles is Bertazzoni's best US market for color. LA's design culture — especially in Silver Lake, Los Feliz, Echo Park, and the Westside — embraces the bold orange, red, and yellow Heritage ranges in ways that more conservative markets don't. We see more Bertazzoni Heritage color calls per month in LA than we do in any other market. The colored panels are why people bought the appliance — we treat them accordingly.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Bertazzoni Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">🔥 Gas Burner Won't Ignite</div><div class="problem-cause">Ceramic igniter failure — either coastal salt air corrosion (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica) or thermal cycling fatigue on the 19,000 BTU power burner. Bertazzoni's sealed burner cap geometry positions the igniter at a specific angle — generic igniters installed at the wrong geometry cause weak or intermittent spark even when new. We use OEM Bertazzoni igniters only.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span></div>
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Inconsistency</div><div class="problem-cause">Temperature sensor drift or calibration offset — the oven runs consistently high or low by 15–25°F. Owners often notice this through baking results before testing the temperature directly. We test with a calibrated probe at multiple setpoints (350°F, 425°F, 500°F) before replacing any component. Many Bertazzoni temperature issues are calibration-only, not sensor replacement.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span></div>
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">🌊 Coastal Igniter Corrosion</div><div class="problem-cause">Salt air accelerates ceramic igniter degradation on all burners, not just the power burner. Coastal Bertazzoni properties (anything within 5 miles of the ocean) typically need full igniter set inspection every 2–3 years. We check all burner igniters on every coastal service call — catching the others before they fail saves a second visit.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-coastal">Coastal LA</span></div>
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">🔵 Induction Zone Dead</div><div class="problem-cause">Inverter board failure for that zone — the most common induction fault across all brands. The inverter converts line power to the magnetic field that heats the cookware. We test each zone's inverter current draw before recommending parts. Board replacement is a fraction of glass surface replacement — correct diagnosis here saves significant money.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span></div>
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">🎨 Color Panel Damage During Service</div><div class="problem-cause">Not a Bertazzoni failure — a service failure. Heritage color panels scratch when contacted with unprotected tools. We see Heritage ranges where a previous technician left visible scratches on the Arancio or Rosso finish. We use felt-backed tools and protective covers on all color-panel work. This is the standard, not the exception.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-color">Heritage Series</span></div>
      <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-title">💨 Convection Fan Bearing Noise</div><div class="problem-cause">Convection fan bearing wear — the fan motor bearings develop noise before the motor fails completely. LA's dusty environment (especially hillside and Valley properties post-Santa Ana) contributes to earlier bearing wear. We replace the full fan motor assembly rather than just the bearing — the bearing and motor are sold together and the labor cost of two visits exceeds the marginal cost of the full assembly.</div><span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
