    <h2 class="section-title">Recent Bertazzoni Repairs Across Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="repairs-grid">
      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni Heritage MAST486GGASNE Range — Silver Lake</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Power Burner Dead, Arancio Panel — Previous Service Left Scratch</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">48" Heritage range in Arancio (orange) — the right rear 19,000 BTU power burner had stopped igniting. Owner mentioned a previous technician had left a light scratch on the front panel. We covered the full front panel with a felt-backed protective sheet before opening anything. Power burner igniter had failed — the ceramic tip had cracked from thermal cycling. Replaced with OEM Bertazzoni igniter for the 19K BTU burner position (different part number than the secondary burners). While we had access, inspected all five igniters — found one secondary igniter showing early corrosion, replaced proactively. Front panel exited the service call without any new marks.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: 2× OEM igniters · Time: 1.5 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni Professional PROF304DFSBIE Dual-Fuel — Brentwood</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Oven Running 20°F Hot, Right Rear Burner Slow to Light</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">30" dual-fuel range — two independent issues. Oven: tested with calibrated probe at 350°F and 425°F — confirmed 20°F high at both setpoints. Temperature sensor reading accurately, so this was a calibration offset. Adjusted the oven temperature calibration through the service menu (Bertazzoni allows ±35°F adjustment). No parts needed. Burner: right rear igniter showed weak spark — cleaned the igniter well (grease accumulation) and tested again. Spark strong, burner lighting immediately. No igniter replacement needed either. Both issues resolved, zero parts cost. Owner had been compensating for the oven temperature for months without realizing calibration was adjustable.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: None (calibration + cleaning) · Time: 1 hour · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni Modern MODCSS304IMXE Induction — Echo Park</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Front Left Zone Dead, Error Code E3</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">30" induction cooktop — front left zone showing E3 fault and not heating. Tested inverter current for all four zones: front left drawing zero current (inverter failure), all others normal. Replaced the front left zone inverter board with OEM Bertazzoni part — the glass surface was undamaged and didn't need assessment. Another company had quoted a full cooktop replacement, citing "induction fault often means surface damage." That's incorrect for E3 — E3 is specifically an inverter fault code. OEM inverter board, same-day. Owner saved roughly $1,400 compared to the cooktop replacement quote.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Inverter board OEM · Time: 1 hour · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni Heritage HERT30GGASXE Range — Los Feliz</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Three Burners Intermittent — Coastal Property Annual Service</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">30" Heritage range in Rosso (red) at a Los Feliz property 4 miles from the coast — not oceanfront but close enough for salt air to matter. Three burners showing intermittent ignition. Full salt air corrosion inspection: all five igniter tips showed surface corrosion at varying stages — two were actively failing (intermittent), one was failing early, two still functional. Replaced all five with OEM Bertazzoni igniters (proactive full set makes sense at this corrosion stage — partial replacement means another call in 6 months). Cleaned all burner wells. Tested all burners at low flame through high. Also inspected the red Rosso front panel for any wear — no issues. Rosso Heritage in excellent condition otherwise.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: 5× OEM igniters (full set) · Time: 2 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni Master MAST30CEVVE Wall Oven — Beverly Hills</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Convection Fan Noise, Baking Uneven</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">30" Master series electric wall oven — grinding noise from the rear during convection cycles, and baking results uneven since the noise started. Convection fan bearing had worn — the grinding noise was the bearing on its way out, and partial bearing seizure was reducing fan speed enough to create uneven airflow. Replaced the full convection fan motor assembly with OEM Bertazzoni part. Temperature-tested at 350°F and 425°F after replacement — even distribution across the full oven cavity. Owner had been avoiding convection mode for weeks. Baking normally again.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Convection fan assembly OEM · Time: 1.5 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">Bertazzoni DW24T4EBPNV Dishwasher — West Hollywood</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Poor Cleaning — Scale Buildup + Spray Arm Blockage</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">Bertazzoni built-in dishwasher — dishes coming out with visible food residue after full cycles. West Hollywood municipal water runs about 280 ppm. Disassembled and inspected the spray arm system: upper spray arm ports 60% blocked with calcium scale deposits, lower arm partially blocked. Filter system had scale accumulation reducing circulation pressure. Performed full descale treatment of the spray circuit, filter, and wash pump intake. Replaced the upper spray arm (the deposits had partially calcified into the arm wall — cleaning alone wouldn't restore full flow). Reset the rinse aid dispenser which had also seized from scale. Post-service cycle ran clean. Set the water softener setting (Bertazzoni has an adjustable setting for local water hardness) to the LA-appropriate level.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Upper spray arm OEM · Time: 1.5 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>
    </div>
